'''''Lithophaga''''', the '''date mussels''', are a [[genus]] of medium-sized [[Marine (ocean)|marine]] [[bivalve]] [[mollusc]]s in the [[family (biology)|family]] [[Mytilidae]].
The shells of species in this genus are long and narrow with parallel sides. The animals [[bioerosion|bore]] into stone or coral rock with the help of pallial gland secretions<ref>"integument (mollusks)."EncyclopÃ¦dia Britannica. 2009. [[EncyclopÃ¦dia Britannica 2006 Ultimate Reference Suite DVD]]</ref>, hence the systematic name ''Lithophaga'', which means "stone-eater". Their club-shaped borings are given the [[trace fossil]] name ''[[Gastrochaenolites]]''.
==Species== Species within the genus ''Lithophaga'' include: * ''[[Lithophaga antillarum]]'' <small>([[Alcide d'Orbigny|d'Orbigny]], 1842)</small> - giant date mussel * ''[[Lithophaga aristata]]'' <small>([[Lewis Weston Dillwyn|Dillwyn]], 1817)</small> - scissor date mussel * ''[[Lithophaga attenuata]]'' <small>([[GÃ©rard Paul Deshayes|Deshayes]], 1836)</small> - attenuated date mussel * ''[[Lithophaga balanas]]'' <small>[[W.H. Dall|Dall]]</small> * ''[[Lithophaga balanus]]'' <small>[[W.H. Dall|Dall]]</small> * ''[[Lithophaga bisulcata]]'' <small>([[Alcide d'Orbigny|d'Orbigny]], 1842)</small> - mahogany date mussel * ''[[Lithophaga cardigera]]'' * ''[[Lithophaga cavernosa]]'' * ''[[Lithophaga cinnamomeus]]'' * ''[[Lithophaga dactylus]]'' * ''[[Lithophaga fasciola]]'' <small>[[W.H. Dall|Dall]], Bartsch, & Rehder</small> * ''[[Lithophaga gracilis]]'' <small>[[Rodolfo Amando Philippi|Philippi]]</small> * ''[[Lithophaga hawaia]]'' <small>[[W.H. Dall|Dall]], Bartsch, & Rehder</small> * ''[[Lithophaga ilabis]]'' <small>([[GÃ©rard Paul Deshayes|Deshayes]])</small> * ''[[Lithophaga lithophaga]]'' <small>([[Carolus Linnaeus|Linne]])</small> * ''[[Lithophaga nigra]]'' <small>([[Alcide d'Orbigny|d'Orbigny]], 1842)</small> - black date mussel * ''[[Lithophaga plumula]]'' <small>(Hanley, 1844)</small> - feather date mussel * ''[[Lithophaga punctata]]'' <small>(Kleemann & Hoeksema, 2002)</small> * ''[[Lithophaga rogersi]]'' <small>S. S. Berry, 1957</small> - Roger's date mussel * ''[[Lithophaga truncata]]'' <small>(Gray, 1843)</small> * ''[[Lithophaga simplex]]'' {{Expand list|date=August 2008}}
